These warnings are coming from [this call to `is_different`](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/c8f22ca269a1f2653ac962fe2bc21105065fd6cd/compiler/rustc_errors/src/annotate_snippet_emitter_writer.rs#L356). The reason this is happening with `AnnotateSnippetEmitter` and not `HumanEmitter` is because `HumanEmitter` [checks for source code availability](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/c8f22ca269a1f2653ac962fe2bc21105065fd6cd/compiler/rustc_errors/src/lib.rs#L410) before it [calls `is_different`](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/c8f22ca269a1f2653ac962fe2bc21105065fd6cd/compiler/rustc_errors/src/lib.rs#L494). Changing [lines 353 to 368 in `annotate_snippet_emitter_writer.rs`](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/c8f22ca269a1f2653ac962fe2bc21105065fd6cd/compiler/rustc_errors/src/annotate_snippet_emitter_writer.rs#L353-L368) to the following fixes the issue:
```rust
let lo = subst.parts.iter().map(|part| part.span.lo()).min()?;
let lo_file = sm.lookup_source_file(lo);
let hi = subst.parts.iter().map(|part| part.span.hi()).max()?;
let hi_file = sm.lookup_source_file(hi);

// The different spans might belong to different contexts, if so ignore suggestion.
if lo_file.stable_id != hi_file.stable_id {
    return None;
}

// We can't splice anything if the source is unavailable.
if !sm.ensure_source_file_source_present(&lo_file) {
    return None;
}

// Account for cases where we are suggesting the same code that's already
// there. This shouldn't happen often, but in some cases for multipart
