I _think_ not - don't we need a total ordering between `AT_EXIT_HOOK_CALLED` and `ACTIVE_ENABLE_CALLS`, similar to the example in https://mara.nl/atomics/memory-ordering.html#seqcst ? 

(I also used https://sabrinajewson.org/rust-nomicon/atomics/seqcst.html as reference, but I didn't fully get [The mixed-SeqCst special case](https://sabrinajewson.org/rust-nomicon/atomics/seqcst.html#the-mixed-seqcst-special-case))

Otherwise, it's possible for the `AT_EXIT_HOOK_CALLED.swap` load to happen-before this `AT_EXIT_HOOK_CALLED`, but that doesn't mean that the following `ACTIVE_ENABLE_CALLS.load` will be ordered before the `fetch_add` so it can read 0.

<details><summary>Minimal Repro for miri</summary>

This will fail `cargo +nightly miri test` on anything other than `SeqCst` for both.

**full disclosure - I used an LLM to create this repro**

```rust
use std::sync::{
    atomic::{AtomicBool, AtomicUsize, Ordering},
    Arc,
};
use std::thread;

#[allow(non_snake_case)]
struct State {
    AT_EXIT_HOOK_CALLED: AtomicBool,
    ACTIVE_ENABLE_CALLS: AtomicUsize,
    EXIT_DONE: AtomicBool,
}

fn enable(s: &State) -> bool {
    // EnableGuard::new()
    s.ACTIVE_ENABLE_CALLS.fetch_add(1, Ordering::SeqCst);

    // Real code: if this is false, enable proceeds toward FlsSetValue(key, ...).
    let would_use_fls_key = !s.AT_EXIT_HOOK_CALLED.load(Ordering::Acquire);

    // Keep ACTIVE_ENABLE_CALLS logically live until the exit hook made its decision.
    while !s.EXIT_DONE.load(Ordering::Acquire) {
        thread::yield_now();
    }

    // Drop EnableGuard
    s.ACTIVE_ENABLE_CALLS.fetch_sub(1, Ordering::SeqCst);

    would_use_fls_key
}

fn at_exit_hook(s: &State) -> bool {
    // free_fls_key_at_exit starts
    let _already_called = s.AT_EXIT_HOOK_CALLED.swap(true, Ordering::AcqRel);

    // Real code: if this observes 0, the hook frees the FLS key.
    let would_free_fls_key = s.ACTIVE_ENABLE_CALLS.load(Ordering::SeqCst) == 0;

    s.EXIT_DONE.store(true, Ordering::Release);

    would_free_fls_key
}

#[test]
fn active_vs_at_exit_needs_seqcst() {
    for i in 0..100 {
        let s = Arc::new(State {
            AT_EXIT_HOOK_CALLED: AtomicBool::new(false),
            ACTIVE_ENABLE_CALLS: AtomicUsize::new(0),
            EXIT_DONE: AtomicBool::new(false),
        });

        let enable_thread = {
            let s = Arc::clone(&s);
            thread::spawn(move || enable(&s))
        };

        let exit_thread = {
            let s = Arc::clone(&s);
            thread::spawn(move || at_exit_hook(&s))
        };

        let enable_would_use_key = enable_thread.join().unwrap();
        let exit_would_free_key = exit_thread.join().unwrap();

        assert!(
            !(enable_would_use_key && exit_would_free_key),
            "bad outcome: enable ignored AT_EXIT_HOOK_CALLED while exit ignored ACTIVE_ENABLE_CALLS (try {})", i
        );
    }
}
```

</details>

